  <span id="freeText1527521766047322726" style="display:none">4.5 Stars <br /><br />What a book! <br /><br />I tried to read this in high school and I just couldn’t seem to get into it – I am so glad I have given this book another go! <br /><br />Having read more Stephen King books including most of The Dark Tower I can finally sink my teeth into this bizarrely brilliant book. This is quite a complex King book and reminds me of The Dark Tower, Insomnia or IT with its fantasy horror genre. <br /><br />As I have said so many times King is one of if not the master of character development and this book is no exception. This book follows a group of characters who couldn’t be more different from each other but all have the same purpose to defeat evil. This is a classic good vs evil story with the craziness of Stephen Kings twists, turns and downright madness. <br /><br />"Dolls with no little girls around to mind them were sort of creepy under any conditions."<br /><br />"Jail,' the big cop said in his stuffy, liquid voice. 'Where anything you bray will be abused against you in a sort of caw."<br /><br />“TAK”<br /><br />By the end of this book it feels like you know each character personally. David is a little hero and I even warmed up to Johnny. Everyone in this book goes through so much during this book and you feel for each one. <br /><br />There is also plenty of guts and gore in this book and it’s enough to make your stomach churn and your toes curls (not in a good way!). This book isn’t for the squeamish! Kings description of death and murder is disgusting and brutal and might be hard to read for some. I think to really understand this book you need to be a seasoned King reader or an avid fantasy/horror reader. <br /><br />If you have tried to read this book before or read it and not understood please try again because once it clicks it’s a beautiful horror show. <br /><br />The only reason this didn’t get my full 5 stars is because the ending was slightly rushed – I think this was the way it was meant to be for effect of how things can end so abruptly and without warning which felt like a theme throughout. I just didn’t want it to end I will 100% be re-reading this one! <br /><br />Overall, I am so glad I tried this book again I defiantly didn’t regret it. <br /></span>
